item.par:
A new &api; named XFind has been added for iterating through &xml;
trees. XFind expressions look somewhat like XPath expressions but are pure
Python expressions. For example finding all images inside links in an &html;
page can be done like this:

example.prog:
node = html.table(class_="example")(
	html.tr(
		html.td("foo"),
		html.td("bar"),
	),
	html.tr(
		html.td("spam"),
		html.td("eggs")
	)
)

ulist.item:
The base &url; is now set correctly when parsing from an &url;
even if the original &url; does a redirect. (This requires ll.url
version 0.11.3).

item.prog:
class foo(xsc.Element):
	empty = False

class xmlns(xsc.Namespace):
	xmlname = "foo"
	xmlurl = "http://www.foo.com/ns/foo"

xmlns.foo = foo

from ll.xist import xsc
class foo(xsc.Element): empty = False
class xmlns(xsc.Namespace): xmlname = "foo" xmlurl = "http://www.foo.com/ns/foo" xmlns.makemod(vars())

if condition:
	align = "right"
else:
	align = None
node = html.div("spam", align=align)
